
# Create a new document from scratch
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/createNewDocument HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "title": "Business Data Cloud - The Data Foundation for Agentic AI",
  "description": "This reference architecture is about Business Data Cloud, the data foundation for agentic AI.",
  "parentId": null,
  "tags": ["genai", "agents", "data"],
  "contributorsUsernames": ["alice", "bob", "fred"],
  "editorState": "{\"state\":{\"someProperty\":\"property value\"}}"
}

###

# Replace the full contributor set of one document
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/setDocumentContributors HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "documentId": "657E1690-0A34-4882-BEDC-25CEA8641BA2",
  "contributorsUsernames": ["bob"]
}

###

# Replace the full tag set of one document
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/setDocumentTags HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "documentId": "657E1690-0A34-4882-BEDC-25CEA8641BA2",
  "tags": ["agents", "data"]
}

###

# Media test setup variables
@documentId = 657E1690-0A34-4882-BEDC-25CEA8641BA2
@drawioAssetId = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
@pngAssetId = 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222

###

# 1) Create metadata row for a draw.io asset (replace IDs if needed)
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "ID": "{{drawioAssetId}}",
  "mediaType": "application/vnd.jgraph.mxfile+xml",
  "filename": "reference-architecture-generative-ai-basic.drawio",
  "document_ID": "{{documentId}}"
}

###

# 2) Upload the draw.io file bytes to the media property
PUT http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets({{drawioAssetId}})/content HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/vnd.jgraph.mxfile+xml
Authorization: Basic alice:

< ./assets/reference-architecture-generative-ai-basic.drawio

###

# 3) Create metadata row for a PNG asset (for download test)
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "ID": "{{pngAssetId}}",
  "mediaType": "image/png",
  "filename": "eda-sap.png",
  "document_ID": "{{documentId}}"
}

###

# 4) Upload PNG bytes
PUT http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets({{pngAssetId}})/content HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: image/png
Authorization: Basic alice:

< ./assets/eda-sap.png

###

# 5) Download PNG bytes
GET http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets({{pngAssetId}})/content HTTP/1.1
Accept: image/png
Authorization: Basic alice:

###

# ------------------------------
# Authorization checks (manual)
# ------------------------------

@authDocId = 657E1690-0A34-4882-BEDC-25CEA8641BA2
@authAssetId = 33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333

###

# A) Users entity is not directly exposed
GET http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Users HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Basic alice:

###

# A1) Documents expand still returns usernames for author + contributors
GET http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Documents({{authDocId}})?$expand=author,contributors($expand=user) HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Basic alice:

###

# A2) Direct POST on Documents is blocked (use createNewDocument action)
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Documents HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "title": "Blocked direct create",
  "description": "Should fail",
  "author_ID": "A0B1C2D3-1111-4A11-8111-111111111111",
  "editorState": "{}"
}

###

# A3) Supported create path via custom action
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/createNewDocument HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "title": "Created via action",
  "description": "Author comes from req.user.id",
  "parentId": null,
  "tags": ["agents"],
  "contributorsUsernames": ["bob"],
  "editorState": "{}"
}

###

# B) Tags are read-only: write attempts should fail
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Tags HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic alice:

{
  "code": "manual-auth-test",
  "label": "Manual Auth Test",
  "description": "Write should fail because Tags is @readonly"
}

###

# C) Contributor can read document (bob must be contributor of authDocId)
GET http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Documents({{authDocId}}) HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Basic bob:

###

# D) Unrelated user cannot read document
GET http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Documents({{authDocId}}) HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Basic fred:

###

# E) Contributor cannot update document
PATCH http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/Documents({{authDocId}}) HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic bob:

{
  "description": "bob should not be able to update this"
}

###

# F) Contributor cannot create document tags directly
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentTags HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic bob:

{
  "document_ID": "{{authDocId}}",
  "tag_code": "data"
}

###

# G) Contributor cannot create document assets directly
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/DocumentAssets HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic bob:

{
  "ID": "{{authAssetId}}",
  "mediaType": "image/png",
  "filename": "should-fail.png",
  "document_ID": "{{authDocId}}"
}

###

# H) Contributor cannot replace contributors via action
POST http://localhost:4004/quickstart/document-service/setDocumentContributors HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic bob:

{
  "documentId": "{{authDocId}}",
  "contributorsUsernames": ["alice", "bob", "fred"]
}